From: stopless-java-gc <noreply@anthropic.com>
Subject: [PATCH 0061/N] metaspace/binList.hpp: BinList32 smallest_word_size = 4 under purecap

`BinListImpl<smallest_word_size, num_lists>` asserts:

  smallest_word_size * sizeof(MetaWord) >= sizeof(Block)

`Block { Block* _next; size_t _word_size; }`. On non-CHERI LP64:
sizeof = 16 = 2*sizeof(MetaWord), so `BinListImpl<2, 32>` works. On
CHERI purecap (with HeapWord/MetaWord = 8-byte struct from 0060),
Block has a 16-byte pointer + 8-byte size_t = 24 bytes + alignment =
32 bytes. The original `2 * 8 = 16 < 32` violates the assertion.

Bump `smallest_word_size` from 2 to 4 under CHERI (4 * 8 = 32 >= 32),
which preserves the BinList semantics with a slightly higher minimum
block size. No correctness impact — just changes the smallest bin
size at the lower end of the metaspace allocator's freelist.

Refs: docs/05_zgc_cheri_collision_report.md (patch 0061)

--- a/src/hotspot/share/memory/metaspace/binList.hpp
+++ b/src/hotspot/share/memory/metaspace/binList.hpp
@@ -196,7 +196,13 @@
 
 };
 
+#ifdef __CHERI_PURE_CAPABILITY__
+// CHERI purecap: Block has a 16-byte pointer + 8-byte size_t = 32 bytes
+// (with alignment). Block's smallest-word-size must accommodate this.
+typedef BinListImpl<4, 32> BinList32;
+#else
 typedef BinListImpl<2, 32> BinList32;
+#endif
 
 } // namespace metaspace
 
